2. Elastic force, or the power ol recoil, arises from the bending of rigid bodies inasmuch as these when bent strive to return to their original form. And indeed it is probable that the elasticity ol the air results mainly from this very cause. It would certainly be reasonable to suppose th'at nitro-aerial and fiery par· ticles are fixed in the ae'rial particles themselves and constitute the more active part of them.
